@00 we have run into the practical power limit
for cooling commodity microprocessors
@01 in the post-PC era the critical resource is energy
@02 measuring time is a safer performance metric than
a rate like MIPS
@04 the energy metric joules is a better metric than watts
@05 watts = joules/sec
006 CMOS: complementary metal oxide semiconductor
@07 dominant tech for IC
@08 dynamic energy: energy that is consumed when transistors
switch state and vice versa
@09 CMOS primary source of energy consumption is dynamic energy
@0a Energy OL capacity load x voltage^2
@0b energy of a pulse during logic transition
0->1->0 or 1->0->1.
@0c energy of single transition
@0d energy 1/2 x Cap x V^2 x freq switched
@0e frequency switched: func of clock rate
@0f cap load/transfer: func of number transistors (?)
connected to output, and technology
@0g tech: determines number of wires/transistors
@06 CMOS: complementary metal oxide semiconductor
